<TITLE> Dravid hospitalised </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com)  Indian batsman Rahul Dravid is unlikely to play any further part in the second Test against Bangladesh after sustaining a nasty blow on the side of the face by a bouncer from Shahadat Hossain during the second day's play on Monday. 'Rahul Dravid was hit by a ball on the side of his face during batting today. He was taken to the (Square) hospital (in Dhaka) for further investigation and a fracture of one of the bones was detected. There are no signs of head injury and his condition is currently stable. He has been kept under observation at the hospital. It is unlikely that he would participate in the rest of the Test match,' Indian team manager Arshad Ayub was quoted as saying in a Bangladesh Cricket Board press release. Dravid had to retire hurt on 111. He featured in a 222-run stand for the third wicket with Sachin Tendu
